## Known Projection Limitations

List ambiguities or missing Core information that may limit SelectNextEpic.

| Limitation | Why It Matters | Recommended Handling |
|---|---|---|

Examples:

- prioritization criteria are underspecified
- desired capabilities are implicit
- dependency semantics are incomplete
- initiative-generation rules are missing
- risk semantics are unclear
- roadmap authority rules are underspecified
- canonical vocabulary is ambiguous

Do not invent missing information to fix these limitations.

## Downstream Use Instructions

When this projection is used by SelectNextEpic:

- Treat this projection as the prioritization frame.
- Treat roadmap completion context as current strategic state.
- Treat the roadmap as advisory, not exhaustive.
- Evaluate existing roadmap epics and newly identified initiatives under the same criteria.
- Do not select an epic merely because it appears first in the roadmap.
- Actively search for hidden dependencies and missing intermediary initiatives.
- Consider existential or systemic risks before ordinary feature progress.
- Prefer initiatives that maximize long-horizon convergence.
- Preserve invariants and established commitments.
- Recommend strategic investigation when uncertainty prevents safe selection.
- Recommend roadmap revision when the roadmap is structurally stale, incomplete, or misaligned.
- Do not modify the roadmap.
- Do not rewrite epics.
- Do not audit the codebase.
- Do not include implementation plans.

## Projection Integrity Checklist

Before finalizing, verify:

- The projection contains prioritization semantics only.
- No completed epic history is included.
- No current roadmap completion state is included.
- No codebase state is included.
- No roadmap epic is selected.
- Every retained statement helps identify, compare, or prioritize future initiatives.
- Every major retained statement traces to the Core North-Star or is clearly marked projection-local.
- Existing roadmap epics and new initiatives can be evaluated under the same framework.
- Hidden dependencies and intermediary initiatives are explicitly supported.
- Roadmap revision and strategic investigation are valid downstream outcomes.
- Canonical vocabulary is preserved.
- Excluded operational and implementation details are not present.
- The projection is compact enough to be passed into SelectNextEpic.